This paper is primarily focused on optimizing activation functions in neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms for this optimization, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments are conducted on image datasets, specifically CIFAR-10 and CIFAR-100, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the potential for these optimized activation functions to improve performance on various tasks, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY).
